The paper discusses a method for global localization in low-cost robots using bioinspired navigation strategies. This involves using proprioceptive sensors for pose estimation and integrating rare visual feedback through a particle filter. This work is relevant to the fields of robotics (cs.RO), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), systems and control (cs.SY), and machine learning (cs.LG).
